<p>Thieves made off with about €88 million worth of French crown jewels from the Louvre in a daylight robbery that has stunned Paris and drawn global attention . New footage circulating on social media appears to show two alleged thieves descending a mechanical ladder or crane near the Seine minutes after the break-in, while the group of four suspects has not been caught . The incident has prompted scrutiny of museum security and captured public imagination in France and abroad .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/Bk3q8pm1gTsB2_5HEhByrsBFrLTr1nn7njz3jje0f0IeHEpqYLAG6uETDnL0XgmbGsyoEpXYMbCMk6wBZHVsvCm7b02GKTe59hNDk8u_VG92RfLlp41YZYF6hE0fTv0urJT1LFV3GUyYfYYpooxcZlW34fra3ow-qigmB6RboUqhbRZn457NlVRFr6nqmSOI606ZcICJWUKqX2nvWh116DA7EJ1bAb0OTAmg7Xs4gG4D9ulwT_nQgByoeV43' alt='Two figures descending on a crane shortly after the Louvre jewellery theft, from circulating video stills' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Escape footage: Video available online shows two people slowly descending a hydraulic lift and looking around frantically minutes after the break-in .</li><li>Security admission: The Louvre&#x27;s director acknowledged staff failed to detect the break-in quickly and said only one camera covered the gallery where the jewels were displayed .</li><li>Public reaction: Parisians and tourists have been riveted by the drama, with media and social posts drawing cultural comparisons to fictional thieves such as Arsène Lupin .</li><li>Market concerns: Experts and commentators are debating whether the historic jewels could ever reappear for sale and where stolen royal pieces might be trafficked .</li></ul><blockquote>Quiet as a whisper - Böcker Machine Works</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Louvre management: The museum acknowledged failures in early detection after the break-in and said it is cooperating with investigators while reviewing procedures. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251024-paris-louvre-heist-video-shows-jewel-thieves-escaping'>France24</a>)</li><li>Böcker (German lift maker): The company has faced intense attention because one of its truck-mounted lifts appears in footage and it has since used the episode in a rapid advertising response. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/24/world/europe/louvre-robbery-german-campaign-bocker.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li><li>Paris residents and commentators: Local reaction mixes shock with fascination, with widespread discussion on social media and in the press. (<a href='https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Europe/2025/1023/louvre-robbery-theft-paris-france-lupin'>The Christian Science Monitor</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/videos/c4g39dnyky1o'>Watch: Video appears to show alleged Louvre jewel thieves escaping</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-24/video-appears-to-show-louvre-thieves-escaping/105929650'>New video appears to show alleged Louvre thieves escaping in broad daylight</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch'>Paris Louvre heist: Video shows jewel thieves escaping • FRANCE 24 English</a> - youtube.com</li><li><a href='https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Europe/2025/1023/louvre-robbery-theft-paris-france-lupin'>The Louvre’s jewels were stolen. Parisians are enthralled by the drama.</a> - csmonitor.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/on-camera-louvre-robbers-dramatic-escape-using-hydraulic-ladder-9508453#publisher=newsstand'>On Camera, Louvre Robbers&#x27; Dramatic Escape Using Hydraulic Ladder</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/speculation-grows-around-whether-the-louvre%27s-stolen-jewels-could-end-up-on-the-market'>Speculation grows around whether the Louvre&#x27;s stolen jewels could end up on the market</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251024-paris-louvre-heist-video-shows-jewel-thieves-escaping'>Paris Louvre heist: Video shows jewel thieves escaping</a> - 